theorem P1_imp_closureInterior_eq_closureInteriorClosure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hP1 : Topology.P1 A) :
    closure (interior A) = closure (interior (closure A)) := by
  -- We prove the two inclusions separately and then use `Set.Subset.antisymm`.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  ·
    exact
      closure_interior_subset_closure_interior_closure (X := X) (A := A)
  ·
    -- First, note that `interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A`.
    have h₁ : closure (interior (closure A)) ⊆ closure A := by
      exact closure_mono (interior_subset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A)
    -- From `P1`, we have `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
    have h₂ :
        closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) :=
      (Topology.P1_iff_closure_subset_closureInterior (X := X) (A := A)).1 hP1
    -- Combine the two inclusions.
    exact Set.Subset.trans h₁ h₂
